From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 16:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] hexagonrpcd: support writable sensor registry callbacks

Modern SensorsPD firmware creates and updates calibration files through
apps_std callbacks that HexagonRPC did not implement. Add fwrite, fsync,
remove, truncate, and rename, and correct the fflush signature.

Expose the complete persistent sensors directory at Qualcomm's expected
registry path so registry data and sns_reg_version resolve exactly as they
do on Android. Restrict all write-mode opens and destructive operations to
that sensor persistence tree; DSP libraries and static configuration remain
read-only.
